text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia truculenta is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to a small area in the  Goldfields-Esperance region of Western Australia.The spreading prickly shrub typically grows to a height of 0.7 to 2.2 metres (2 to 7 ft). It blooms from August to September and produces yellow flowers.
